        jLabel7.setFont(new java.awt.Font("Segoe UI", 0, 18)); // NOI18N
        jLabel7.setText("<html><body> Nilgiri, often referred to as the \"Blue Mountains,\" stands as a majestic peak in the Chittagong Hill Tracts region of Bangladesh, near Cox's Bazar. <br> At an elevation of about 2,350 feet, Nilgiri offers more than just a stunning panoramic view of the surrounding landscapes and the Bay of Bengal. What truly sets<br>  it apart is the Nilgiri Resort, popularly known as Nilachol. Perched on the hill, Nilachol is not only a vantage point for breathtaking sunsets and cloud-kissed peaks<br>  but also a tranquil haven for those seeking serenity. The resort offers comfortable accommodation, making it a perfect retreat for nature enthusiasts and adventure<br>  seekers alike. Nilachol provides an immersive experience, combining the thrill of being on the hilltop with the soothing ambiance of the surrounding greenery, making< br> it an essential stop for anyone exploring the beauty of Cox's Bazar.  </body></html>");
        jPanel1.add(jLabel7, new org.netbeans.lib.awtextra.AbsoluteConstraints(610, 370, 880, 270));

        jLabel8.setFont(new java.awt.Font("Segoe UI", 0, 18)); // NOI18N
        jLabel8.setText("<html><body>\nMeghla, nestled in the heart of the picturesque Bandarban district in Bangladesh, is a captivating destination that seamlessly blends natural beauty with cultural allure.<br> Surrounded by lush greenery and rolling hills, Meghla offers a serene escape for nature enthusiasts and adventure seekers alike. The centerpiece of Meghla is the Meghla Tourist Complex, a hub of recreational activities<br> and attractions. Boasting a breathtaking lake, the complex provides opportunities for boat rides amidst scenic landscapes. Visitors can explore the Eco Park, home to a variety of indigenous plant species<br> and wildlife, creating a harmonious blend of conservation and tourism. Meghla is not just a destination; it's a gateway to the enchanting landscapes of Bandarban, where each moment invites you<br> to discover the rich tapestry of nature and culture in this hillside haven.\n\n\n\n\n</body>\n</html>");
        jPanel1.add(jLabel8, new org.netbeans.lib.awtextra.AbsoluteConstraints(590, 1170, 900, -1));

